# The Fibonacci number
```python
def fibonacci(n):
    """Generate the nth Fibonacci number"""
    if n == 0:
        return 0
    elif n == 1:
        return 1
    else:
        return fibonacci(n-1) + fibonacci(n-2)
```
This function calculates the nth Fibonacci number by recursively calculating the two preceding numbers. It is a classic demonstration of the technique, simple enough to be grasped by any beginner. Try it with different inputs!
